pr_title: Interface to interact with brickschema PR #1
pr_body:
Updates:
- Reworked `load_brick_file` and `new_brick_file` to fit under the `VersionedGraphCollection` implementation.
- Made `BrickStore.graph` to refer to the entire `VersionedGraphCollection` as to generally still work with the rest of the code without having to change variable names. 
- `BrickStore.schema` is now a file path. (Made that the case in the testing also).
- To access the graph isolated from the Brick metadata, the new `get_project()` method was made in `BrickStore`.
- Added `undo_brick` and `redo_brick`. _**NOTE: Currently, these are operators, but the plan is to integrate this with ctrl-z and ctrl-shift-z instead.**_
- Added conditionals to `undo` and `redo` so it doesn’t error when there is nothing to undo/redo.
- Updated `add_brick` and `remove_brick` to work with undo/redo versioning.
- Created operator `serialize_brick()` that for now saves to the `/schema/` directory. _**NOTE: Currently, there is no way to specify a file path and name to save to, but the plan is to add this soon.**_
- Removed namespace URL from the namespace selector. _**NOTE: This feature will become pointless as the plan is to create an entirely new namespace editor/manager tab.**_
- Silenced known rdflib_sqlalchemy TypeError warning (when using `VersionedGraphCollection`) with the `logging` package.
- I had to merge with the main branch because I needed to put `Brick.ttl` into `.git-ignore` which caused merge conflicts, so I resolved it.

pr_title: Interface to interact with brickschema PR #2
pr_body:
- Created "save" and "save as' options to serialize brick project
- Created settings toggle for namespace editing
- For now, filtered a few namespaces out of the namespace Enum (a better way to approach this may be just to populate the Enum with namespaces from the `brick.tool` rather than from `brick.data)`
- Creating an entity now gives the option to specify a label

pr_body:
- reformat the UI a little.
- improve filter for namespaces by ignoring any namespaces that included unwanted URL’s ("brickschema.org", "schema.org", "w3.org", etc).
- improve hierarchy in viewer by adding UI option to set the hierarchy display type.
    - sort by system
    - sort by location
    - sort by all equipment
    - show all points
- move `namespaces` and `brick_equipement_classes` data into `BrickStore`, so that it isn't refreshed every time the Blender UI changes.
- drop down to select what type of thing you are adding (location, system, equipment, point) and populates the entity options with the relative type.
- simple filter for blacklisting populating the attribute of entitles that are part of the Brick ontology.

pr_body:
- Update feature, core, and tool tests
- Data is now stored regularly in `BrickStore` and instead parsed in props
- Refresh viewer now reloads both screens by default
- Fix Brick tool
    - `get_convertable_brick_spaces` now returns a set
    - Fix assign brick reference bug from last merge
- Fix Brick Core
    - Fix error where `view_brick_class` was run instead of `brick.run_view_brick_class`
